Title: Series: Four landscapes with penitent saints
Description: St Antony of Egypt visiting St Paul the Hermit; the two saints sitting on either side of a stone desk in front of Paul's cave at l; the pig next to Antony; above the valley at left the raven bringing Paul bread; from a series of four plates. Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Herman van Swanevelt
Curator's comments: BM has a complete set of the series.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (15.I)
Associated names: Representation of: St Paul the Hermit
Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
